<br>
Nowadays, I'm blessed with friends, wealth and pretty nice gear.  I usually pass up on rolling on things I wouldn't equip.  However, I still don't agree with NBG in pick-up groups, even if I won't roll on most things.  I don't feel it's right for ANYONE to not have a shot at a reward, as it was a team effort.  In a perfect world, melee loot and caster loot would be balanced everywhere, and everyone would be able to get an equal shot at something, and everyone would be perfectly honest.  But, that's not how it is in Norrath.  And, there will be those who say 'Well, casters don't need equipment really.'  Have you ever seen an Enchanter trying to do CC down to King naked?  Ever see how much a Wizard can nuke with no mana gear?  No, I likely won't die if a level 45 mob attacks me while on CR, while a Warrior might.  However, in order to do my best, I do need more than 800 base HP.<br>
<br>
Honestly, if you think that someone who is against NBG in your group reflects a bad reputation, I suggest you reconsider the fact that Kunark is ~80% melee loot (and VL camps are fairly stingy on that, as well), and maybe you might realize this makes you look a bit greedy yourself.<br>
